TOPIC:Popular browsers and their JavaScript engines. 
                                              

Opera:
      Uses the Blink JavaScript engine. Blink is an open-source, high-performance JavaScript engine  that  is used by Opera and other Chromium-based browsers. It is known for its speed and efficiency.


Microsoft Edge:
     Uses the Chakra JavaScript engine. Chakra is a proprietary, high-performance JavaScript engine that is used by Edge and other Chromium-based browsers. It is known for its speed and efficiency.



Apple Safari:
    Uses the JavaScriptCore JavaScript engine. JavaScriptCore is an open-source, high-performance JavaScript engine that is used by Safari and other WebKit-based browsers. It is known for its speed and efficiency.


Mozilla Firefox:
     Uses the SpiderMonkey JavaScript engine. SpiderMonkey is an open-source, high-performance JavaScript engine that is used by Firefox and other Gecko-based browsers. It is known for its speed and flexibility.


Google Chrome:
     Uses the V8 JavaScript engine. V8 is an open-source, high-performance JavaScript engine that is used by Chrome and other Chromium-based browsers. It is known for its speed and efficiency.
